## What I Did

In this lab, I prepared the DialogSum dataset and converted dialogues into instruction-style summarization prompts.

Since the original pre-trained PEFT checkpoint was not available in my personal Google Colab environment, I created a local LoRA adapter on top of FLAN-T5.

Then I wrapped the PEFT model with a PPO ValueHead and created a frozen reference model. The reference model represented the original policy, while the PPO model was the trainable policy.

A RoBERTa-based hate speech classifier was used as the reward model. The model classified text into two labels:

- `nothate`
- `hate`

The `nothate` logit was used as the positive reward signal during PPO training.

The PPO training loop generated summaries, evaluated them with the reward model, and updated the trainable policy based on the reward score.

